<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and
        Camshaft - Clean, Inspect, and Measure - Measure Crankshaft End Play
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="measure" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Measure Crankshaft End Play</title>
        <figure id="f3350016518" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk06/K06034.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankshaft end play measurement</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para id="s1616" count="1">Mount magnetic base of a
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_428.xml" xrefid="t335001603">dial indicator set</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001603"/>
                on a flat engine surface.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Push crankshaft toward the rear of the engine and put tip of dial indicator on the
                crankshaft end.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Zero dial indicator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lightly pry crankshaft toward the front of the engine and then away. Pry between the
                crankshaft counter weight and crankcase main bearing caps.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, use new main bearing cap bolts whenever main bearing cap bolts are
                    removed.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">See crankshaft end play
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_426.xml" xrefid="t335001601">Specification</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001601"/>.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If crankshaft end play exceeds maximum specification, replace thrust main bearing (# 7 upper).
                        Install and
                        <hotlnk document="eges3351_421.xml" xrefid="s1624">torque new main bearing cap bolts</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="s1624"/>. Repeat steps 1 through 4.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If crankshaft end play is less than minimum specification, loosen main bearing caps and
                        reposition bearings. Install and torque new main bearing cap bolts. Repeat steps 1 through 4.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
